newcol.steps:
\[
\begin{split}
f(a) &= \phi_a(q(x - a) + r)
\\&
\class{steps}{\cssId{step0}{= \phi_a(q)\cdot\phi_a(x - a) + \phi_a(r)}}
\\&
\class{steps}{\cssId{step1}{= q(a)(a - a) + r}}
\\&
\class{steps}{\cssId{step2}{= r.}}
\end{split}
\]

statement.paragraphs:
)
Let $k$ be a field, $f$ a polynomial in $k[x]$.  Then, $a \in k$
is a root of $f$ if and only if $(x - a)$ divides $f$ in $k[x]$.
